      <div class="logo">PDF</div>
      <div>
        <h1>PDF Editor — Free · Open-Source · Privacy-First</h1>
        <p class="lead">A local-only desktop PDF editor for Linux. No uploads. No telemetry. Portable AppImage. Essential PDF operations made fast and private.</p>
        <div class="badges">
          <span title="License">MIT</span> · <span title="Platform">Linux AppImage</span> · <span title="Built with">Python, PySide6, PyMuPDF</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="grid" role="region" aria-label="Product summary and download">
      <section>
        <article class="card" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Product">
          <h2 itemprop="name">Why choose this PDF Editor</h2>
          <ul class="features" itemprop="description">
            <li>Privacy-first. All processing happens locally on your device. No cloud uploads.</li>
            <li>Completely free. MIT license. No hidden costs or watermarks.</li>
            <li>Portable single AppImage. Run without installation. Ideal for quick use and offline environments.</li>
            <li>Core features: delete, split, merge, reorder pages, PDF→images, compress, add/remove password, redact areas, add watermark, edit metadata, extract text.</li>
            <li>Designed for users who care about security, privacy and auditability. Source available to inspect.</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="cta" role="presentation">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/anuragrana/pdf_editor_desktop_app/blob/master/PDF_Editor-x86_64.AppImage" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Download AppImage (no install)</a>
            <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/anuragrana/pdf_editor_desktop_app" rel="noopener" target="_blank">View on GitHub (source & docs)</a>
          </div>

          <div class="meta">
            <strong>Quick start</strong>
            <ol style="margin:6px 0 0 18px">
              <li>Download AppImage. `chmod +x PDF_Editor-x86_64.AppImage`</li>
              <li>Run: `./PDF_Editor-x86_64.AppImage`</li>
              <li>Or run from source: `pip install -r requirements.txt` then `./run.sh` or `python3 -m src.main`</li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <div class="meta" style="margin-top:12px">
            <strong>Audience</strong>
            <div>Privacy-conscious users, auditors, sysadmins, developers, and organisations that cannot use cloud editors.</div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="card" style="margin-top:18px">
          <h3>Features (high level)</h3>
          <ul class="features">
            <li>Delete, split, merge, reorder pages</li>
            <li>Area redaction with color options</li>
            <li>Password add/remove</li>
            <li>Watermark and metadata editing</li>
            <li>PDF → JPEG conversion and compression</li>
            <li>Logs & status pane and desktop notifications</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card" style="margin-top:18px">
          <h3>Technical</h3>
          <p class="meta">Built with Python 3.8+, PySide6 GUI, PyMuPDF (fitz) for PDF processing, Pillow for images and pikepdf for advanced ops. Licensed under MIT.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card" style="margin-top:18px">
          <h3>Security & privacy</h3>
          <p class="meta">All operations are performed locally. No telemetry and no cloud uploads. Source code is public for audit and contribution.</p>
        </article>
      </section>

